Click on the header to list the pages related to the patching of Emacs.
Such patches are necessary when extensions are added on the C level.

* ApplyingPatches -- Beginner information on working with patches.
* SecurEmacs -- extend Emacs with GNU TLS
* DynamicallyExtendingEmacs -- let Emacs load shared libraries (so/dll)
* PixelDrawing -- draw pixels from Lisp
* HackerGuide -- introduction to Emacs core
* Native Interfaces to Databases:
** MySql
** PostGreSQL
* MultiTTYSupport -- support for multiple display devices in GnuEmacs

Also see EmacsFromArch for some Emacs branches available using ArchVersionControl.
